a) Why is it important to configure an enable (EXEC mode) password on a switch?

Answer:

Protects access to privileged EXEC mode (Router# / Switch#)

Prevents unauthorized configuration changes

Enhances network security

Ensures only authorized users can manage the device



---

b) Explain the role of VLAN1 in a switch’s initial configuration.

Answer:

VLAN1 is the default VLAN on a switch

All ports belong to VLAN1 initially

Used for management and initial communication

Default IP address is assigned to VLAN1 for remote access



